    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="502"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.91/11–344</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Under Secretary of
                        State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-03">November 3,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Dr. Daftary, the Iranian Chargé d’Affaires, called this afternoon at his
                    request.</p>
                <pb facs="0479" n="467" xml:id="pg_467"/>
                <p>He stated that he had been instruction [<hi rend="italic">instructed</hi>] to
                    call upon me immediately to advise me of the deplorable relations between Iran
                    and the Soviet Union. He said that the Russians captured many Iranian troops and
                    police in the northern part of the country, had taken their weapons and
                    ammunition, and that the highways had been cut off and large segments of the
                    population left without water and food. He characterized the situation as most
                    distressing and critical and stated that his Government was appealing to the
                    United States to take a firm position with Russia immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>E[<hi rend="smallcaps">dward</hi>] S[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >tettinius</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
